Definition: /kaʊ/ - (properly) An adult female of the species Bos taurus especially one that has calved.(formerly inexact but now common) Any member of the species Bos taurus regardless of sex or age including bulls and calves.Beef the meat of cattle as food.Any bovines or bovids generally including yaks buffalo etc.A female member of other large species of mammal including the bovines moose whales seals hippos rhinos manatees and elephants.A woman considered unpleasant in some way particularly one considered nasty stupid fat lazy or difficult.A chock a wedge or brake used to stop a machine or car. /kaʊ/ - (chiefly in the passive voice) To intimidate to daunt the spirits or courage of. /kaʊ/ - A chimney cowl.
/ˈɹæpaɪn/ - The seizure of someone's property by force pillage plunder.To plunder.
